      {
        "id": 2061345,
        "name": "Kevin_S_hin",
        "username": "k_s_h_i_n",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/7cd45c/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2016-11-21T20:09:49.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The 02 showed incredibly, of course extremely youthful.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=562936&amp;iNote=3969591\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2002 Giacomo Conterno Barolo Riserva Monfortino</strong></a> <em>- Italy, Piedmont, Langhe, Barolo (11/29/2013)</em><br>\n<em><a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/event.asp?iEvent=23202\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Impromptu lunch \u2013 96 Salon, 02 Monfortino, 02 Jayer Gilles Echezeaux and etc. (Friend\u2019s house)</a></em>: My first experience with this monumental wine. I had no idea what to expect. Surprisingly opaque for a Monfortino. Intense sweet dark fruits, black cherries, dried blackberries, roasted meat, rose, tar, basking spices and surprisingly strong note of balsamico. Excellent concentration, extremely sweet intense fruit expression, dense yet silky, bright acidity, sweet tannins and long finish. I was surprised by the intense sweet fruits and incredible concentration. There is a hint of VA expressed as strong Balsamic note. For me, this adds lovely sweetness and intensifies the fruit expression. This is a monumental wine with a long life ahead. <em><strong>(98 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
