      {
        "id": 2061377,
        "name": "Sarah Kirschbaum",
        "username": "Sarah_Kirschbaum",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/9d8465/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2016-11-21T20:43:04.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Agreed the '02 is a beautiful and lovely young Monfortino.  With that bottle, I would absolutely NOT decant it.  We had a bottle in Italy with lunch a year or so ago, which we decanted for several hours, then began drinking slowly.  After only a short time, maybe less than an hour, it shut down hard and remained firmly closed the rest of the time it was open, which was another 10 hours or so since we re-corked it and left it in the apartment while we went to dinner.</p>",
