      {
        "id": 2062438,
        "name": "Kevin_S_hin",
        "username": "k_s_h_i_n",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/7cd45c/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2016-11-22T23:02:35.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This is very mineral/iron driven Monfortino.  If the fruit is shy, it may not be all that enjoyable.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=800135&amp;iNote=5317620\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2005 Giacomo Conterno Barolo Riserva Monfortino</strong></a> <em>- Italy, Piedmont, Langhe, Barolo (11/7/2015)</em><br>\n<em><a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/event.asp?iEvent=29724\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">2015 Villa d\u2019Este Wine Symposium - Kelly and Kevin\u2019s excellent adventure; 11/3/2015-11/9/2015 (Villa D\u2019este, Lake Como)</a></em>: Joe W. served this blind to us. Slightly dry sweet cherry fruits, rose and strong presence of mineral. I am actually thinking Chateau Musar! Very iron and mineral driven wine, quite precise and structured. I wonder when Balsamic note will show. It will always have plenty of iron/mineral. <em><strong>(96 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n<li>\n<a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=800135&amp;iNote=3134929\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2005 Giacomo Conterno Barolo Riserva Monfortino</strong></a> <em>- Italy, Piedmont, Langhe, Barolo (11/5/2012)</em><br>\n<em><a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/event.asp?iEvent=19603\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Kelly and Kevin\u2019s excellent adventure before WWS 2012; 11/4/2012-11/11/2012 (La Morra)</a></em>: Definitely a Monfortino but close resemblance to the 08 CF, just deeper tone and more of tar, rose, iron and balsamico. Still quite open, not big and impressive but seamless. Beautiful silky texture and noticeable tannins. <em><strong>(96 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
